# Construct vector search queries

Just as you did in the previous step, you can explore the search results using an aggregation pipeline.

## Querying with the aggregation builder

Using the aggregation builder, or the MongoDB Shell, you can construct a pipeline that uses the `$search` stage to query the `vectorsearch` index.

Add the following code for the `$search` stage.

```js
public async searchBooks(query: string): Promise<Book[]> {
    const aggregationPipeline = [
        {
            $search: {
            index: "vectorsearch",
            knnBeta: {
                vector: [ vector goes here ],
                path: "embeddings",
                k: 20
            }
            }
        }
    ];
    const books = await collections?.books?.aggregate(aggregationPipeline).toArray() as Book[];
    return books;
}
```

The stage uses the `vectorsearch` index. Rather than using the 'text' operator as we did for full-text searches, we are using the <Link to="https://www.mongodb.com/docs/atlas/atlas-search/knn-beta/">knnBeta</Link> operator this time.

For now, this stage will break. You will need to pass it a vector in the `vector` property.

Paste the following vector to replace the `vector goes here` text.
